{"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib10VariantRefV","extendedModule":"GLib","title":"takeRef()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/takeRef()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantref\/takeref()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this function is helpful.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":".  We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where the value that is being returned already exists)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, the style of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" API makes it likely that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for newly-created "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" instances, the user can be saved some","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"typing if they are allowed to return a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" with a floating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them.  The caller"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" instance.  If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference.  If ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"an additional reference on top of that one is added.  It is best to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"avoid this situation."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef/takeRef()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantref\/takeref()","type":"topic","title":"takeRef()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"ide